{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"LIVE RECURRENCE (strongest evidence yet): closing 4de6 just now, the completion verifier FAILED with a criterion marked unmet because 'No such test exists anywhere in the test suite ... exhaustive searches for TOCTOU, drift, close-ticket, HEAD-move, completion-race, and 4de6 in tests/ all returned no matches' — for the criterion 'a test that moves HEAD in the verify→sign window'.\n\nThat test PLAINLY EXISTS and is collectible on origin/main:\n  tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_close_default_pins_head_4de6.py::test_default_close_pins_head_across_a_concurrent_commit\n  (committed in 55e2b5cca, the 4de6 carrier; `pytest --co` collects 2 tests; the file name literally contains '4de6' and the test moves HEAD mid-verify via a racing verify stub and asserts the close signs against the pre-move sha).\n\nSo the verifier's 'exhaustive search for 4de6' missed a file NAMED *_4de6.py containing the ticket id. This is the same TEST-EXISTENCE false-negative characterized above (ad9f), reproduced on a different ticket. It also confirms the impact direction that matters most: the verifier BLOCKS complete work (false FAIL), and the block is non-deterministic (ad9f fl\\ipped FAIL→PASS on retry). Directly motivates BOTH fixes scoped here: temperature 0 (reduce the sampling variance that flips these searches) + recorded verify_at_sha (so a false-FAIL can be checked against the actual verified tree from stored data)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784843869420229001,"uuid":"50b886cf-ca49-472c-9d7e-161c466f4b28"}